Hague Says U.K. Government Won’t Waver on Deficit Reduction

-- B y   A n d r e w   A t k i n s o n
-- 
2011-10-02T09:29:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-02/hague-says-u-k-government-won-t-waver-on-deficit-reduction.html
Foreign Secretary  William Hague  vowed
the British government will not waver in its commitment to
cutting the budget deficit.  “The answer to excessive borrowing and debt cannot be more
borrowing and debt,” he told Sky News television today. “This
chancellor won’t waver, this government won’t waver.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andrew Atkinson in London at 
